Betrayal broker risked billions for inferiority
A treacherous embezzler.
This is how French banking giant Société Générale, the owner of Komerční banka, describes his former employee Jerome Kerviel.
He lost almost 5 billion euros.
But it seems that Kerviel was just a big player who wanted to compete with his colleagues and certainly not incompetent.
Unlike all major banking houses, he recognized early on the crisis in the American mortgage market.
"He's mentally weaker," his superiors said, sending the police after him.
