We wait in line for about half an hour.
Around 140,000 drivers have not yet exchanged their driving licences in Prague.
It takes 20 days to issue a new card.
However, it is possible to apply for extradition within a reduced period of five days.
In this case, however, the driver will pay five hundred crowns.
Motorists who do not have to change their license before the end of the year and leave the road without a valid driver's license will be subject to a fine from January.
The offender will pay a maximum of 2,000 crowns.
A police officer can also deal with an offence.
In the event of an administrative offence, the fine will amount to CZK 2,500.
