Under the Spanish, Cuba was the bastion of their conquest of America.
Columbus called it the most beautiful place ever seen by the human eye.
Havana became a storehouse and a repository of treasures that the Spanish looted in America and transported to Europe.
Then came the American era.
Hotel Nacional grew up at the very end of the 1920s.
