Which insurance is right for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a considerable expense, which depends on various factors, such as age, condition, gender, length of possession of a driver's license, type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insured.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract, which stipulates that the insurance company will receive an agreed insurance amount in return for taking charge of the payment of damages in the event of an insured event.
Insurance premium is the price of insurance, which is determined taking into account various factors such as age, status, gender, length of possession of a driver's license, type of vehicle that is insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the greater the likelihood of a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their prudence.
In the same way, insurance companies found that married people had fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of driving and thus the likelihood of it having an accident.
Increasing the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when setting the premium price.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best suits his profile of the insured.
We will show here the most important variables for choosing this or that type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of the insured, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face a variety of disadvantages, such as little driving experience and a short driving license when they want to negotiate premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks at a premium discount so as to get insurance coverage for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would assume the client's complicity in the payment of the insurance event.
"The amount of the insurance claim payment provided by the client will be pre-determined when determining the premium price, which will be the higher the lower the deductible would be," explains Luis Noguera, chief executive of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other participants of the operation so that the client insures against damage caused to other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of the vehicle.
Recommendation.
If you are under the age of twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid crashes as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce insurance premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the insurance company has.
Malus, on the other hand, is an increase in the above-mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
After crossing the twenty-five-year limit, drivers have it easier when they go to arrange insurance, as the client's risk index decreases, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
“Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance when an accident occurs, nor when driving,” assures the director of a European company in Spain, adding that most accidents occur in the second year of driving, when the “newcomer’s fear” has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as the clientele with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with a premium discount (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," notes Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks at a premium discount (which is 150 euros) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It should be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a considerable expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us best in relation to our personal situation.
